<topic template="Default" lasteditedby="rbwinst" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Farm Climate Dialog Box</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Farm Climate Dialog Box</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Farm Climate</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box is used to specify a time series of climate data. The dialog box is displayed by selecting </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Model|Farm Process|Farm Climate...</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> The </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Farm Climate</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box can only be displayed if </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Rooting depth (</text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="When_to_Read_Flags" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">IRTFL</link><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">)</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> is set to </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Calculated (3), or Precipitation (</text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="When_to_Read_Flags" anchor="IPFL" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">IPFL</link><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">)</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> is set to </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Climate time series (3)</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, or </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Consumptive use (</text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="When_to_Read_Flags" anchor="ICUFL" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">ICUFL</link><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">)</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> is set to </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Calculated (3)</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The climate data that are required are the maximum and minimum temperature, the precipitation, and the reference evapotranspiration. These data are described in </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="References_Cited" anchor="FMP1" styleclass="Reference" translate="true">Schmid and others (2006)</link><text styleclass="Reference" translate="true"> starting on p. 48.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The climate data are used to calculate consumptive use (potential crop evapotranspiration), root depth, and precipitation using empirical equations. </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="When_to_Read_Flags" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">IRTFL</link><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">, </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="When_to_Read_Flags" anchor="IPFL" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">IPFL</link><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">, </text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">and</text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true"> </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="When_to_Read_Flags" anchor="ICUFL" styleclass="Strong" translate="true">ICUFL</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> determine which ones are calculated.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Most commonly, the Penman-Monteith estimate of potential evapotranspiration is used as a reference evapotranspiration. </text></para>
  </body>
